
[1]courtier

   COURTIER, n. [from court.]

   1. A man who attends or frequents the courts of princes.

   2. One who courts or solicits the favor of another; one who flatters to
   please; one who possesses the art of gaining favor by address and
   complaisance.

   There was not among all our princes a greater courtier of the people
   than Richard III.
